 anthropology of religion itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChristianity. 0aHealingxReligious aspectsxProtestant churches. 0aHealingzNorth AmericaxReligious aspectsxProtestant churches. 0aHumanities. 0aLiberalism (Religion)xHistory. 0aLiberalism (Religion)zNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aProtestant churcheszNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aProtestantismzNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aProtestantism. 0aReligion. 0aSpiritual healing. 0aTherapeutics. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh  a20th century anthropology.  a20th century christianity.  a20th century protestants.  aanthropology and christianity.  acanada and religion.  achristian history.  achristian missionary.  achristian salvation theory.  achristian students.  achristianity and protestants.  aethnography and religion.  aliberal christianity.  aliberal protestantism.  aliberal protestants.  amedical missionaries.  amedicine and christianity.  amedicine and religion.  areligious history.  areligious studies students.  ascience and religion.  asecularism and religion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095044340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520950443/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles